data.name: infoButton4.InfoText
data.value:
Additional ffmpeg parameters can go here.
By default your parameters are added to the end of list (i.e. before specifying the output file).
You can specify "before:" to place that particular parameter before other parameters (excluding -ss and -t): before:-af "volume=10dB"
Be mindful of the final command in the preview box before running!

data.name: infoButton2.InfoText
data.value:
This sets the speed using the setpts video filter.
IMPORTANT: This does not affect audio right now, but you can manually set it in additional options: Use '-filter:a atempo=x' where x is your speed multiplier (cannot be less than 0.5 or more than 100). FURTHER: You may want to set your desired FPS using the '-r (fps)' option in additional options, as FFmpeg will otherwise drop frames it doesn't need.
CONTROLS: Hold Shift while sliding for finer control Hold Alt while sliding for even finer control

data.name: infoButton1.InfoText
data.value: Constant Rate Factor / Constant Quantiser Parameter These are similar quality-based encoder modes: - CRF is used by Software (CPU) encoders for adaptive quality and better efficiency - CQP is used by Hardware (GPU) encoders with fixed compression for faster performance Generally: higher value = lower quality but smaller filesize. The results will vary across encoders. For example, AV1 works better at lower bitrates: h264_nvenc, CQP 24 ≈ av1_nvenc, CQP 32-34 (roughly).
